Provide the `generate-print-members` CMake custom command and pseudo-target, backed by cmake/scripts/generate_print_members.py, that reads $BUILDDIR/generated/ctags/tags.json (goal 03) directly -- with no intermediate class inventory -- and writes one print_members.cpp per namespace bucket under $BUILDDIR/generated/print_members/ plus a `source_files` manifest listing them. Running the pseudo-target always drives `ctags-json` first; at configure time the same ctags+python commands run only when NEED_GENERATION holds (source_files missing or any listed cpp absent). The generation command must also run whenever any generated cpp is older than tags.json -- e.g. after a manual `ctags-json` refresh -- so stale printers are never compiled; making this timestamp condition work is the remaining work.
